---
// Philosophy.astro — Forest journal editorial section
---
<section class="philosophy" id="philosophy">
  <div class="philosophy__inner">

    <div class="philosophy__sidebar">
      <span class="label">Our Philosophy</span>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <p class="philosophy__sidebar-text">
        We believe luxury is measured in stillness, not in things.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="philosophy__body">
      <div class="philosophy__col philosophy__col--narrow">
        <p class="philosophy__lead">
          The Canopy House began not as a hotel, but as a question:
          What if a building could belong to the forest as much as it occupied it?
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="philosophy__col philosophy__col--wide">
        <p class="philosophy__copy">
          Sited on twelve acres of second-growth Sitka spruce and Douglas fir, our twelve rooms were designed
          with the rhythms of the natural world as the primary blueprint. We work with local craftspeople
          using timber felled by last winter's storms — wood with history. Our kitchen gardens sit where
          logging roads once scarred the earth, now healed and productive.
        </p>
        <p class="philosophy__copy">
          There is no check-in desk. No uniformed concierge. There is a lending library of field guides.
          A fire pit that is never cold between October and April. A breakfast that changes with what the
          forager brings through the door. We think of ourselves as stewards of a place that was beautiful
          long before we arrived and will remain so long after.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="philosophy__pull">
      <blockquote class="philosophy__quote">
        "We measure prosperity in the return of songbirds to the canopy."
      </blockquote>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
.philosophy {
  padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
  background: var(--cream);
  position: relative;
}

.philosophy::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  height: 1px;
  background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--amber), transparent);
  opacity: 0.4;
}

.philosophy__inner {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 2rem;
}

.philosophy__sidebar {
  margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
}

.philosophy__sidebar-text {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--green-mid);
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.philosophy__body {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.6fr;
  gap: var(--space-lg);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  align-items: start;
}

.philosophy__col {
  padding-top: 0.5rem;
}

.philosophy__lead {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.2vw, 1.8rem);
  font-weight: 400;
  line-height: 1.4;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.philosophy__copy {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--ink-light);
  margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
}

.philosophy__copy:last-child {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.philosophy__pull {
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(74,93,74,0.15);
  padding-top: var(--space-md);
}

.philosophy__quote {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
  font-weight: 300;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--green);
  text-align: center;
  padding: 0 var(--space-md);
}

.philosophy__quote::before {
  content: '\201C';
  color: var(--amber);
}

.philosophy__quote::after {
  content: '\201D';
  color: var(--amber);
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .philosophy__body {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .philosophy {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }
}
</style>